                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@RuchirBaronia A debugger allows you to step through a program line by line to see which methods are called and how variables are changed. IDEs should have some tools to do this. See &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.vogella.com/tutorials/EclipseDebugging/article.html&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer&quot;&gt;vogella.com/tutorials/EclipseDebugging/article.html&lt;/a&gt; for example.&lt;/span&gt;

